HEADWORD: Hoppet
<hw>Hop"pet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A hand
basket; also, a dish used by miners for measuring ore.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An infant in arms.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hopping</ent>⟦br⟧
